      "content": "If the seller tries to back out or if the inspection reveals issues, the escrow agent will follow a specific process to resolve the situation. They'll typically review the escrow agreement and the terms of the sale to determine the best course of action. If the seller is unable to fulfill their obligations, the escrow agent may release the earnest money to you, the buyer, as a refund or as a credit towards the purchase price. However, the agent must follow the terms of the escrow agreement and any applicable local laws or regulations to ensure a fair and transparent resolution.",
